00x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/james-cameron-avatar@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/james-cameron-avatar@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/james-cameron-avatar@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/james-cameron-avatar@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/james-cameron-avatar@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> If you thought <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/avatar"><em>Avatar</em></a> and its sequel <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/avatar-the-way-of-water"><em>The Way Of Water</em></a> were long, get ready for <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/avatar-fire-and-ash"><em>Fire and Ash</em></a> .</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/film-reviews/avatar-the-way-of-water-review-3366050">&#39;Avatar: The Way Of Water&#39; review: bold, beautiful and very, very blue</a></strong></li></ul><p> According to franchise creator and director James Cameron, <em>Fire and Ash</em> will be the longest film in the <em>Avatar</em> trilogy to date, but there&#39;s a good reason why. For context, the original 2009 <em>Avatar</em> film ran for two hours and 42 minutes, while 2022&#39;s <em>The Way Of Water</em> ran for three hours and 12 minutes.</p><p> Speaking to <a href="https://www.empireonline.com/movies/news/avatar-fire-ash-writers-split-film-way-of-water-exclusive/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Empire Magazine</em></a> recently, Cameron shared that <em>The Way Of Water</em> had “too many great ideas” that were introduced that required being split into two films. </p><figure id="attachment_3840627" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3840627" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3840627" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/avatar-james-cameron@2000x1270.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/avatar-james-cameron@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/avatar-james-cameron@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/avatar-james-cameron@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/avatar-james-cameron@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/avatar-james-cameron@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/avatar-james-cameron@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3840627" class="wp-caption-text"> &#39;Avatar&#39; director James Cameron. Credit: Ian West/PA Images via Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p> Cameron explained: “In a nutshell, we had too many great ideas packed into act one of [ <em>The Way Of Water</em> ]. <em>The Way of Water</em> , in retrospect, was moving like a bullet train, and we weren&#39;t drilling down enough on character. So I said, &#39;Guys, we&#39;ve got to split it.&#39; [ <em>Fire and Ash</em> ] will actually be a little bit longer than [ <em>The Way Of Water</em> ].”</p><p> Amanda Silver, a co-writer on both <em>The Way of Water</em> and <em>Fire And Ash</em> added that the films characters will only benefit from having their character arcs develop over two films: “The characters needed to breath.这些电影不仅仅是推进的情节和华丽的奇观。 I mean, these are real characters.”</p><p> <em>Avatar: Fire and Ash</em> is set for release on December 19.</p><p> Last month, Cameron seemingly confirmed that the <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/avatar-fire-and-ash-will-reportedly-include-anti-ai-disclaimer-3840626">upcoming film will open with an anti-AI disclaimer</a> : “No generative AI was used in the making of this movie”. James Cameron&#39;s aversion to AI shouldn&#39;t come as much of a surprise, as the filmmaker <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/guillermo-del-toro-on-ai-it-can-do-semi-compelling-screensavers-and-thats-that-3796123">in July 2023 spoke out against the technology</a> , referencing his sci-fi classic <em>Terminator</em> when asked what he thought of AI&#39;s rise in the entertainment industry: “I warned you guys in 1984, and you didn&#39;t listen.” </p><figure id="attachment_3366054" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3366054" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3366054" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Avatar_Way_Of_Water.jpg" alt="头像" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Avatar_Way_Of_Water.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Avatar_Way_Of_Water-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Avatar_Way_Of_Water-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Avatar_Way_Of_Water-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Avatar_Way_Of_Water-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Avatar_Way_Of_Water-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3366054" class="wp-caption-text"> &#39;Avatar: The Way Of Water&#39;. CREDIT: Disney/20th Century Studios</figcaption></figure><p> Cameron added that he doesn&#39;t believe the technology behind AI will be able to replace writers, saying: “It&#39;s never an issue of who wrote it, it&#39;s a question of, is it a good story?”</p><p> Elsewhere, James Cameron recently confirmed that <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/michelle-yeoh">Michelle Yeoh</a> will <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/james-cameron-confirms-michelle-yeoh-will-not-be-in-avatar-fire-and-ash-3783550">not be starring in the movie but she will feature in its sequel</a> . Yeoh was first announced to join the <em>Avatar</em> franchise in 2019. Cameron previously <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/james-cameron-shot-avatar-3-and-4-early-to-avoid-stranger-things-ageing-issues-3370601">revealed he shot scenes for the third and fourth films in the franchise in advance</a> to avoid <a href="https://www.nme.com/series/stranger-things"><em>Stranger Things</em></a> -style ageing issues with the younger cast members. He also previously revealed that he was <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/james-cameron-says-he-could-end-avatar-franchise-early-if-sequel-doesnt-do-well-3345278">prepared to end the franchise after the third film</a> if <em>The Way Of Water</em> wasn&#39;t a box office success. </p><div class="td_block_wrap tdb_single_content tdi_86 td-pb-border-top td_block_template_2 td-post-content tagdiv-type" data-td-block-uid="tdi_86" data-io-article-url="https://www.nme.com/news/film/avatar-fire-and-ash-will-reportedly-include-anti-ai-disclaimer-3840626"><div class="tdb-block-inner td-fix-index"><div class="td_block_wrap tdb_single_content tdi_86 td-pb-border-top td_block_template_2 td-post-content tagdiv-type" data-td-block-uid="tdi_86" data-io-article-url="https://www.nme.com/news/film/avatar-fire-and-ash-james-cameron-warns-fans-it-might-not-be-what-they-signed-up-for-3830548"><div class="tdb-block-inner td-fix-index"><p> In a <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/film-reviews/avatar-the-way-of-water-review-3366050">four-star review</a> of <em>Avatar: The Way Of Water</em> for <em>NME</em> , Ali Shutler wrote: “Bigger, bolder and definitely better than the original, <em>Avatar: The Way Of Water</em> pushes the technical boundaries of cinema without feeling like a science experiment.确实需要在最大的屏幕上通过一对尴尬的3D眼镜看到它。 Unlike its predecessor though, you won&#39;t forget this experience in a hurry.”</p></div></div></div></div><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/avatar-fire-and-ash-will-be-the-franchises-longest-film-yet-james-camero